# ==========================================
# Frontend Environment Variables (OPTIONAL)
# ==========================================
#
# ✅ BEST PRACTICE:
# Frontend gets ALL configuration from backend API endpoint:
# GET /api/config
#
# Backend returns:
# - googleClientId (from backend .env)
# - apiUrl (from backend .env)
# - features flags
# - app info
#
# ❌ DO NOT create .env file in frontend unless needed for:
# - Local development proxy override
# - Build-time constants (not runtime config)
#
# ==========================================
# Optional: Local Development Override
# ==========================================
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
#
# NOTE: If not set, frontend will use:
# - Development: Vite proxy (/api -> localhost:3001)
# - Production: Same origin (/api -> Nginx proxy)
#
# ==========================================
# Security Notes
# ==========================================
# ✅ Safe in frontend .env:
# - VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID (public, client-side only)
# - VITE_API_URL (public endpoint)
#
# ❌ NEVER put in frontend .env:
# - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET (backend only!)
# - JWT_SECRET (backend only!)
# - Database credentials (backend only!)
# - Any private keys or secrets
#
# All sensitive data stays in backend/.env only!
